<TITLE> Police recover 4 bombs in Barguna </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Barguna, May 6 (bdnews24.com)  A bomb exploded on Thursday in a house of Amtali upazila in Barguna, from where the police seized four more bombs after they were informed. The police said that the incident had occurred at the house of one Abdul Jalil Molla at Churikata village of the upazila in the morning. The police arrested Abdul Jalil and his mother-in-law Salina Begum for possession of bombs. The locals said that Jalil is Jalal Fakir's niece's husband. Jalal Fakir, they said, is the president of Amtali upazila BNP. Prime minister Sheikh Hasina inaugurated the national service project to provide jobs for the unemployed people at around 2pm at Barguna circuit house premises. Abdul Jalil, a sub-inspector of the Amtali Police Station told journalists that a hand made bomb had exploded at Jalil's house at around 11am. The police, being immediately informed, recovered another four bombs from the house, the police officer added. The arrestees are being questioned at the police station, the police officer said. bdn
